gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Cavaliers 112, Bucks 100
gameRecap.excerpt: The Cavaliers defeated the Bucks, 112-100, as they improved to 27-16. Donovan Mitchell led the Cavaliers with 32 points, eight rebounds, and six assists as Jarrett Allen added his fourteenth consecutive double-double with 24 points, 14 rebounds, and two blocks. Giannis Antetokounmpo led the Bucks with 22 points, 10 rebounds, and nine assists as Damian Lillard totaled 22 points, three rebounds, and three assists. The loss brings Milwaukees three-game win streak to an end, as they move to 31-14.
